name: language_sql_data_utf8_bom
description: |
  U+FEFF appears at the start of an otherwise ordinary value. Some decoders
  strip it as a byte-order mark even when it is application data, causing stored
  and queried values to differ.
format: hex
decode-as: utf8
unicode-meta:
  code-units: 8
  code-points: 6
  scalar-values: 6
  legacy-grapheme-clusters: 6
  extended-grapheme-clusters: 6
tags:
  - "language"
  - "sql"
  - "sql-data"
  - "utf8"
  - "byte-order-mark"
  - "normalization"
  - "round-trip"
---
ef bb bf "value"
